================================================================================
Third-Party Acknowledgements
================================================================================

NyayaLens stands on the shoulders of the following open-source projects. We
studied their architecture, metric definitions, and test fixtures while
building our own custom engine. None of their code is included verbatim in
this repository unless explicitly noted.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
IBM AI Fairness 360 (AIF360)
  Source:  https://github.com/Trusted-AI/AIF360
  License: Apache License 2.0
  Used as: Reference implementation for Consistency score (k-NN, Zemel et al.
           2013) and Reweighing (Kamiran/Calders 2012); test oracle fixtures
           for SPD, DIR, EOD numerical correctness (see
           backend/tests/fixtures/aif360_oracles.json).
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Microsoft Fairlearn
  Source:  https://github.com/fairlearn/fairlearn
  License: MIT License
  Used as: Reference for edge-case handling patterns (errors="coerce",
           empty-group NaN coercion in MetricFrame.difference/.ratio);
           additional numerical test fixtures for metric validation.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
UChicago DSSG Aequitas
  Source:  https://github.com/dssg/aequitas
  License: MIT License
  Used as: Reference for 80% rule (EEOC) threshold logic and
           policy-oriented disparity framing.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Holistic AI
  Source:  https://github.com/holistic-ai/holisticai
  License: Apache License 2.0
  Used as: Reference for clean binary-group metric API shapes (SPD, DIR,
           EOD functional signatures).
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Microsoft Presidio
  Source:  https://github.com/microsoft/presidio
  License: MIT License
  Used as: Direct runtime dependency (presidio-analyzer). We use its
           PatternRecognizer architecture and the pre-built India-specific
           recognizers (Aadhaar, PAN, GSTIN, Passport, Voter ID, Vehicle
           Registration) as part of the NyayaLens PII Pre-Scrubber.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Oracle Guardian AI
  Source:  https://github.com/oracle-samples/guardian-ai
  License: Universal Permissive License (UPL) v1.0
  Used as: Reference for privacy-aware fairness patterns (aggregated
           subgroup statistics, not individual records).
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Google PAIR: What-If Tool / LIT
  Source:  https://github.com/PAIR-code/what-if-tool
           https://github.com/PAIR-code/lit
  License: Apache License 2.0
  Used as: UX inspiration for counterfactual interaction and metric display
           patterns (post-MVP reference only; no code reused).
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Microsoft Responsible AI Toolbox
  Source:  https://github.com/microsoft/responsible-ai-toolbox
  License: MIT License
  Used as: UX inspiration for bias heatmap and cohort management patterns
           (no code reused; original Flutter implementation).
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Google Agents CLI / ADK
  Source:  https://github.com/google/agents-cli
  License: Apache License 2.0
  Used as: Methodology reference for post-MVP agentic remediation workflows.
           Not integrated in v1.0.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Runtime Python dependencies (see backend/pyproject.toml for current versions)
include fastapi, uvicorn, pydantic, numpy, pandas, google-generativeai,
firebase-admin, presidio-analyzer, reportlab, and tenacity. Each is used under
its respective upstream license.

Runtime Dart/Flutter dependencies (see frontend/pubspec.yaml) include
flutter_riverpod, go_router, dio, fl_chart, freezed, firebase_auth, and pdfx.
Each is used under its respective upstream license.

================================================================================
Data Sources
================================================================================

- shared/sample_data/placement_synthetic.csv is NyayaLens-generated synthetic
  data with seeded disparities for demonstration. No real individuals.
- shared/sample_data/german_credit.csv (if included) derives from the UCI
  Machine Learning Repository "Statlog (German Credit Data)" dataset.
- shared/sample_data/placement_real_anchor.csv is intentionally NOT committed
  to this repository (see .gitignore). Any real placement data used must be
  de-identified, manually approved, and stored outside version control.
